item.title: Neitiznot - Rhubarb, Jerba/Pegasus
item.dc:creator: @Ares1 Ares_
item.description:
@Ares1 wrote:

[quote=“thakillah, post:20, topic:524616”][quote author=Ares_ link=topic=643236.msg4332268#msg4332268 date=1373830413]
To disable the RSA Encryption keys from the client side go to your stream class.

Then search doKeys()

You should see this then:

public void doKeys() {
		int i = currentOffset;
		currentOffset = 0;
		byte abyte0[] = new byte[i];
		readBytes(i, 0, abyte0);
		BigInteger biginteger2 = new BigInteger(abyte0);
		BigInteger biginteger3 = biginteger2.modPow(RSA_EXPONENT, RSA_MODULUS);
		byte abyte1[] = biginteger3.toByteArray();
		currentOffset = 0;
		writeWordBigEndian(abyte1.length);
		writeBytes(abyte1, abyte1.length, 0);
	}

Then you see this line

Change it to this

Now compile and you will be able to login.
[/quote]

Don’t remove RSA.[/quote]

Most people don’t have a clue what RSA is even, yet a lone to enable it all server sided. RSA has been removed from clients for ages till recently no need to make a fuss about it.

Read full topic
